    "abstract": "In this article, we propose GIFT-COFB, an Authenticated Encryption with\nAssociated Data (AEAD) scheme, based on the GIFT lightweight block cipher and\nthe COFB lightweight AEAD operating mode. We explain how these two primitives\ncan fit together and the various design adjustments possible for performance and\nsecurity improvements. We show that our design provides excellent performances in\nall constrained scenarios, hardware or software, while being based on a provably-secure\nmode and a well analysed block cipher.",
    "keywords": [
      "GIFT",
      "COFB",
      "authenticated encryption",
      "lightweight",
      "lower bound"
    ],
    "category": "Secret-key cryptography",
